Description: The clinic I went to see in Borneo is run by an Indonesian organization called ASRI (Alam Sehat Lestari). It is not religious! The founders are an American doctor and an Indonesian dentist. You can visit their website here:
   http://www.alamsehatlestari.org/

But a better overview comes from this article written in 2012…
https://psmag.com/social-justice/save-the-trees-well-save-your-life-46121

…or you could listen to the 30-minute package I did for the BBC last year:
http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b08hnly0

  You can make a donation by bank transfer here…
   http://www.alamsehatlestari.org/donate/

…or if you want to do it online they also have a US fundraising arm called Health in Harmony:
 
https://healthinharmony.org/
https://healthinharmony.org/programs/asri/

And you can make donations online: 
https://healthinharmony.org/donate/

I hope you think this is a worthwhile cause, and even if you don’t, I do! -- so please do it to support my channel. The orang utans and the sick children will thank you!
